Class NodeReachabilitySegmentationResolver

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ig.segmentation.network.segment.NodeReachabilitySegmentationResolver
  • All Implemented Interfaces:

    public class NodeReachabilitySegmentationResolver
extends java.lang.Object
implements IgSegmentationResolver
    Node Reachability Resolver will check whether an address is reachable through the host machine and validate the segment accordingly.

      • setLocalNodeName

        public NodeReachabilitySegmentationResolver setLocalNodeName(java.lang.String localNodeName)
                                                      throws IgSegmentationException
        Sets the local node host name

        This is a required field in case setLocalNodeAddress(java.net.InetAddress) is not used.

        The host name can either be a machine name, such as "java.sun.com", or a textual representation of its IP address. If a literal IP address is supplied, only the validity of the address format is checked.

        Parameters:
        localNodeName - Local host node name
        Returns:
        this for chaining.
        Throws:
        IgSegmentationException

      • setLocalNodeNetworkInterfaceToUse

        public NodeReachabilitySegmentationResolver setLocalNodeNetworkInterfaceToUse(java.net.NetworkInterface localNodeNetworkInterface)
        Sets network interface to be used, in-case local host node IP is associated with multiple network interfaces.

        This is optional, but it is always a good practice to provide the network interface explicitly else it will pick up the first available interface associated with the IP address.

        Parameters:
        localNodeNetworkInterface - Network interface address for the local node
        Returns:
        this for chaining.
